10 These words of dark colour  
11 I saw them written at the top of a door;  
12 for which I: “Master, their sense is hard to me.”

13 And they to me, as a prudent person:  
14 “Here it is fitting to leave all suspicion;  
15 all cowardice it is fitting that here be dead.

